                " No information about source of uncertainties"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/By authors/ Ni-57 can most easily be produced by",
                "helium-3 bombardment of natural iron by the reaction",
                "Fe-56(He3,2n)Ni-57 the occurrence of Fe-56 in natural",
                "iron being 92%. Ni-56 can be produced by the",
                " (alpha,2n) reaction on Fe-54, but since natural iron",
                "contains less than 6% of this isotope the helium-3",
                "reaction on Fe-56 was preferred. However, since the",
                "decay scheme of Ni-56 is more favorable for medical",
                "work it will later replace the Ni-57 in this experiment"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
